.TH "LOOKIT" "1" "Mar 2026" "lookit v0.4.0-dev" ""

.SH NAME
lookit-graph - Output link graph in DOT format


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBlookit graph [path] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate a Graphviz DOT representation of the inter-document link graph.
Nodes are markdown files, edges are links between them (standard markdown
links and [[wikilinks]]). Pipe to dot, neato, or other Graphviz tools to
render as an image.

.PP
An interactive graph is also available at /graph when using "lookit serve".


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for graph


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB-c\fP, \fB--config\fP=""
	config file path

.PP
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	enable verbose logging

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	disable colors (ascii theme)

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	color theme (light|dark|auto|ascii)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  lookit graph
  lookit graph | dot -Tpng -o links.png
  lookit graph ~/docs | dot -Tsvg -o graph.svg
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBlookit(1)\fP


